The paper discusses the use of artificial neural networks (Multi-Layer Perceptron) for time series modeling and forecasting, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence research. The paper also proposes a pruning process to improve the performance of the MLP, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning for reducing the complexity of models. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization and learning phases, which are also common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.SI (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well.
